766
01:09:17,120 --> 01:09:19,970
Don't move. I'll fetch the candles.

767
01:09:20,160 --> 01:09:22,970
Eat your gumbo. Oh, fiddlesticks.

768
01:09:43,430 --> 01:09:45,250
Dinner by candlelight.

769
01:09:46,120 --> 01:09:47,070
There.

770
01:10:02,370 --> 01:10:04,790
So, was that the storm or the ghosts?

771
01:10:05,890 --> 01:10:08,130
Well, say what you will about spirits.

772
01:10:08,200 --> 01:10:10,200
I've always wondered
if there wasn't something...

773
01:10:10,280 --> 01:10:11,800
we could learn from them.

774
01:10:12,200 --> 01:10:13,580
Like a spell?

775
01:10:16,140 --> 01:10:18,720
I have great respect for your husband.

776
01:10:18,790 --> 01:10:21,660
And whatever he thinks
happened to him, he's fighting it.

777
01:10:21,740 --> 01:10:23,620
What did happen to him, Violet?

778
01:10:23,690 --> 01:10:25,510
You haven't touched your gumbo.

779
01:10:25,580 --> 01:10:26,550
What have you done to him?

780
01:10:26,630 --> 01:10:29,570
I made that special for you,
and you haven't even touched it.

781
01:10:29,640 --> 01:10:30,660
What have you done?

782
01:10:30,730 --> 01:10:33,280
He is my husband, and I am his wife...

783
01:10:33,360 --> 01:10:35,740
and I will do to him whatever I wish to do!

784
01:10:35,820 --> 01:10:37,850
He's not safe in this house.

785
01:10:37,960 --> 01:10:39,750
What, what...

786
01:10:39,820 --> 01:10:41,230
What is this?

787
01:10:41,610 --> 01:10:42,890
You've done something.

788
01:10:42,960 --> 01:10:45,510
He's not safe in this house. Not with you.

789
01:10:45,570 --> 01:10:47,620
- This is my house.
- I'm taking him, Violet.

790
01:10:47,690 --> 01:10:48,640
No!

791
01:10:54,500 --> 01:10:56,610
Too late. Not again.

792
01:10:57,420 --> 01:11:00,200
You little whore. He's mine.

793
01:11:02,280 --> 01:11:05,540
Keep him in this house.

794
01:11:06,000 --> 01:11:07,150
Keep him in this...

795
01:11:07,980 --> 01:11:09,300
He's mine!

796
01:11:14,160 --> 01:11:15,410
"Protection."

797
01:11:27,990 --> 01:11:29,640
Where's the record?

798
01:11:38,510 --> 01:11:39,720
Oh, God.

799
01:11:45,740 --> 01:11:46,890
Got it.

800
01:11:52,020 --> 01:11:53,330
You bitch.

801
01:12:03,930 --> 01:12:05,230
Time to go.

802
01:12:20,050 --> 01:12:21,330
Come on, Ben.

803
01:12:21,400 --> 01:12:23,700
I'm going to get you out of here.
Just hold on.

804
01:12:48,700 --> 01:12:49,910
Damn it!

805
01:12:51,060 --> 01:12:52,310
Keep him in this house.

806
01:12:57,500 --> 01:12:58,680
Hold on.

807
01:13:14,520 --> 01:13:15,770
Caroline?

808
01:13:27,710 --> 01:13:28,920
Oh, shit!

809
01:13:43,970 --> 01:13:45,220
Caroline.

810
01:13:49,480 --> 01:13:50,910
Come on, Ben!

811
01:13:53,860 --> 01:13:55,040
We've got to hide you, Ben.

812
01:14:12,800 --> 01:14:15,420
I'm gonna get help. I won't leave you.

813
01:14:18,250 --> 01:14:19,300
Okay?

814
01:14:30,380 --> 01:14:31,620
Caroline?

815
01:14:37,740 --> 01:14:40,550
You think you can take him
out of this house?

816
01:14:41,070 --> 01:14:43,400
You think you're stronger than me?

817
01:14:44,550 --> 01:14:47,650
You've no idea how strong I am, Caroline.

818
01:14:53,190 --> 01:14:54,400
Caroline!

819
01:14:58,510 --> 01:15:01,380
You're just making it harder on yourself!

820
01:15:03,150 --> 01:15:04,610
Where are you?

821
01:15:11,150 --> 01:15:13,220
You can't get away, Caroline.

822
01:15:14,410 --> 01:15:16,040
You understand me?

823
01:15:16,590 --> 01:15:19,020
You'll never get out of here, child.

824
01:15:20,430 --> 01:15:21,640
Caroline?

825
01:15:24,820 --> 01:15:25,770
Caroline!

826
01:15:26,570 --> 01:15:28,170
Stop right there!

827
01:16:20,250 --> 01:16:21,460
Thank you.

828
01:16:25,970 --> 01:16:27,060
Luke!

829
01:16:28,220 --> 01:16:29,650
Jesus Christ.

830
01:16:31,890 --> 01:16:34,100
She tried to kill me.

831
01:16:35,480 --> 01:16:36,950
She had a gun.

832
01:16:37,300 --> 01:16:39,640
She knows I know. Ben's in trouble.

833
01:16:39,710 --> 01:16:43,320
He's still at the house.
Call the police, Luke. I left him.

834
01:16:43,550 --> 01:16:45,180
We got to get back out there.

835
01:16:45,240 --> 01:16:46,590
The hell we do.

836
01:16:46,680 --> 01:16:48,250
I left him there.

837
01:16:49,340 --> 01:16:51,990
You didn't leave anyone. Okay? Slow down.

838
01:16:52,350 --> 01:16:55,130
Tell me what happened.
She tried to kill you?

839
01:16:57,020 --> 01:16:58,140
Sorry.

840
01:17:00,120 --> 01:17:01,590
Mrs. Devereaux.

841
01:17:01,670 --> 01:17:03,450
To what do I owe the...

842
01:17:04,610 --> 01:17:07,260
Heard from Caroline? Why would she have...

843
01:17:08,640 --> 01:17:10,140
What's going on?

844
01:17:12,420 --> 01:17:14,450
Okay. What happened tonight?

845
01:17:16,030 --> 01:17:17,590
Hang on a second.

846
01:17:17,890 --> 01:17:19,710
We need to record this.

847
01:17:23,360 --> 01:17:25,460
Hurting him? Hurting him how?

848
01:17:28,480 --> 01:17:31,230
What do you mean?
What are you talking about?

849
01:17:33,610 --> 01:17:35,230
I am listening to you.

850
01:18:41,990 --> 01:18:43,630
Good night, child.

851
01:19:06,540 --> 01:19:08,580
A hell of a thing, isn't it?

852
01:19:09,520 --> 01:19:11,280
See, everywhere you look...

853
01:19:12,370 --> 01:19:14,470
it's a whole new world all around you.

854
01:19:14,540 --> 01:19:16,940
It's like being born.

855
01:19:17,550 --> 01:19:20,270
Or dying. Of course, I wouldn't know.

856
01:19:41,880 --> 01:19:44,150
Hush, darling. I know it's hard.

857
01:19:47,640 --> 01:19:48,850
We're home!

858
01:19:48,920 --> 01:19:51,530
He's missing. She's hidden him somewhere.

859
01:19:52,500 --> 01:19:54,290
Where is he, Caroline?

860
01:19:56,120 --> 01:19:58,450
It's not him, it's me.

861
01:19:59,600 --> 01:20:01,900
You want to sacrifice me.

862
01:20:02,580 --> 01:20:03,700
Where is he, Caroline?

863
01:20:03,760 --> 01:20:05,650
Why are you helping her?

864
01:20:08,020 --> 01:20:09,850
- Is everything ready?
- No.

865
01:20:09,910 --> 01:20:12,150
I can't start anything till I know where he is.

866
01:20:12,210 --> 01:20:14,290
What's our tale if he gets away?

867
01:20:15,130 --> 01:20:16,630
Caroline...

868
01:20:16,690 --> 01:20:19,860
you will tell me exactly
where my husband is.

869
01:20:20,210 --> 01:20:24,110
There's nothing anybody can do
for him, so there's no need to try.

870
01:20:25,020 --> 01:20:26,360
Where is he?

871
01:20:27,960 --> 01:20:29,790
Where is he, Caroline?

872
01:20:34,290 --> 01:20:36,180
He's in the garden shed.

873
01:20:40,220 --> 01:20:43,280
Don't scratch her up any more
than she already is.

874
01:20:46,720 --> 01:20:48,400
She's teaching you.

875
01:20:48,800 --> 01:20:51,920
You help her kill me,
and she'll teach you how.

876
01:20:52,000 --> 01:20:52,940
Ben knew, too, didn't he?

877
01:20:53,020 --> 01:20:54,450
That's enough, Caroline.

878
01:20:54,520 --> 01:20:56,860
You want to shoot me, shoot me.

879
01:20:56,920 --> 01:20:58,960
Stop right there, Caroline!

880
01:21:08,260 --> 01:21:10,290
I want my father's picture.

881
01:21:12,770 --> 01:21:14,360
I want it with me.

882
01:21:15,140 --> 01:21:16,320
Please.

883
01:21:31,330 --> 01:21:32,600
Jesus. All right.

884
01:21:32,670 --> 01:21:35,740
You want your picture,
I'll get your goddamn picture.

885
01:21:39,000 --> 01:21:44,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

886
01:21:57,470 --> 01:21:58,460
Fuck!

887
01:22:05,160 --> 01:22:07,230
Violet, she's going outside!

888
01:22:15,180 --> 01:22:16,320
Violet!

889
01:22:28,300 --> 01:22:29,610
She's here!

890
01:22:30,800 --> 01:22:32,620
Quick! Go get her! Help me!

891
01:22:35,340 --> 01:22:36,550
Come on.

892
01:22:48,560 --> 01:22:50,310
She's fixed the door!

893
01:23:00,650 --> 01:23:02,990
Violet, I can't get up the stairs!

894
01:23:16,910 --> 01:23:19,150
You try to use my tricks on me?

895
01:23:24,080 --> 01:23:25,190
On me, huh?

896
01:23:52,210 --> 01:23:54,030
No!

897
01:24:24,920 --> 01:24:26,350
<i>911 emergency.</i>

898
01:24:26,420 --> 01:24:28,560
My name is Caroline Ellis.

899
01:24:28,630 --> 01:24:30,740
I'm at 1750...

900
01:24:31,610 --> 01:24:33,750
Bayou Chapelet in Terrebonne Parish.

901
01:24:33,820 --> 01:24:35,930
I need police and paramedics.

902
01:24:36,000 --> 01:24:38,520
There are people hurt here. We're trapped.

903
01:24:38,870 --> 01:24:40,190
Please hurry.

904
01:24:47,040 --> 01:24:48,150
<i>- What time is it?
- Jill.</i>

905
01:24:48,230 --> 01:24:50,110
<i>- Jill.
- Cary?</i>

906
01:24:50,200 --> 01:24:51,540
Jill, I'm in trouble.

907
01:24:51,750 --> 01:24:52,790
Caroline?

908
01:24:52,860 --> 01:24:54,010
It's real.

909
01:24:54,620 --> 01:24:57,010
<i>- It's all real.
- You're where? What?</i>

910
01:24:57,530 --> 01:24:59,230
I'm in the Devereaux house.

911
01:25:00,130 --> 01:25:02,160
<i>What's real? What...</i>

912
01:25:03,420 --> 01:25:04,470
Jill?

913
01:25:12,390 --> 01:25:13,620
Caroline!

914
01:25:15,000 --> 01:25:20,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
You can't get away, Caroline.

915
01:25:25,950 --> 01:25:27,330
Oh, God, no.

916
01:25:28,220 --> 01:25:29,470
Caroline.

917
01:25:36,740 --> 01:25:40,670
"Chalk, sulfur, blood, hair."

918
01:25:51,810 --> 01:25:52,960
Sulfur.

919
01:25:55,530 --> 01:25:56,670
Candle.

920
01:25:56,900 --> 01:25:58,080
Chalk.

921
01:26:16,040 --> 01:26:17,190
Hurry!

922
01:26:19,020 --> 01:26:20,160
Circle.

923
01:26:21,800 --> 01:26:22,890
Eyes.

924
01:26:24,170 --> 01:26:26,270
Four eyes. North, south.

925
01:26:27,050 --> 01:26:29,420
Hurry! Oh, God, please.

926
01:26:30,020 --> 01:26:31,370
What's next?

927
01:26:35,400 --> 01:26:36,490
Hair.

928
01:26:44,000 --> 01:26:49,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
My child...
I believe you broke my legs.

929
01:26:53,260 --> 01:26:54,920
You can't touch me.

930
01:26:55,400 --> 01:27:00,140
You can't get near me. See this?
This is your spell of protection.

931
01:27:00,620 --> 01:27:02,570
Is that what that is now?

932
01:27:03,760 --> 01:27:06,540
And who exactly gave you that spell?

933
01:27:07,060 --> 01:27:09,700
All that circle protects is you...

934
01:27:10,830 --> 01:27:12,070
from leaving it.

935
01:27:18,550 --> 01:27:20,000
You stay back!

936
01:27:20,110 --> 01:27:22,020
I'll kill you! You stay away!

937
01:27:22,420 --> 01:27:24,840
We've been waiting for you, Caroline.

938
01:27:25,140 --> 01:27:27,140
Waiting for you to believe.

939
01:27:27,790 --> 01:27:30,250
It doesn't work if you don't believe.

940
01:27:32,630 --> 01:27:34,220
<i>It is time, Lord.</i>

941
01:27:34,710 --> 01:27:37,190
<i>From the dry dust out of these chains.</i>

942
01:27:37,270 --> 01:27:38,510
I don't believe.

943
01:27:40,910 --> 01:27:41,860
I don't.

944
01:27:45,270 --> 01:27:46,730
I think you do.

945
01:27:46,870 --> 01:27:51,240
The weakness is the flesh.
The flesh, the flesh.

946
01:27:51,380 --> 01:27:53,560
I don't believe.

947
01:27:55,610 --> 01:27:56,790
I don't...

948
01:27:59,510 --> 01:28:01,340
I don't believe in it.

949
01:28:09,760 --> 01:28:11,950
The flesh. The coil.

950
01:28:12,020 --> 01:28:13,130
I don't believe.

951
01:28:13,370 --> 01:28:15,440
The frail. The weak.

952
01:28:16,020 --> 01:28:17,430
I don't believe.

953
01:28:19,420 --> 01:28:20,530
I don't...

954
01:28:21,590 --> 01:28:22,540
No.

955
01:28:25,330 --> 01:28:26,650
Oh, my God.

956
01:28:31,890 --> 01:28:33,460
I don't believe!

957
01:28:35,550 --> 01:28:37,070
I don't believe!

958
01:28:37,690 --> 01:28:39,220
I don't believe!

959
01:28:39,770 --> 01:28:41,200
I don't believe!

960
01:30:04,620 --> 01:30:06,180
Thank you, child.

961
01:30:15,880 --> 01:30:17,060
Cecile?

962
01:30:18,290 --> 01:30:19,740
You all right?

963
01:30:21,360 --> 01:30:23,180
I'm fine now, Justify.

964
01:30:26,050 --> 01:30:28,100
A fair bit harder than the lawyer,
wasn't she?

965
01:30:28,170 --> 01:30:30,000
It's harder every time.

966
01:30:30,830 --> 01:30:33,190
They just don't believe like they used to.

967
01:30:33,260 --> 01:30:34,690
Got to get them riled up.

968
01:30:40,040 --> 01:30:42,730
I told you I wanted a black one this time.

969
01:30:43,150 --> 01:30:45,290
You know the black ones never stay.

970
01:30:46,610 --> 01:30:48,580
Beggars can't be choosers.

971
01:30:49,490 --> 01:30:51,720
I think it fits you beautifully.

972
01:30:52,430 --> 01:30:55,430
It's better than Violet, or Grace, even.

973
01:30:57,580 --> 01:31:00,610
We'll get used to it. We always do.

974
01:31:15,180 --> 01:31:18,210
The thing folks don't understand
about sacrifice...

975
01:31:19,920 --> 01:31:21,610
Get me out of here.

976
01:31:23,030 --> 01:31:25,030
...sometimes it's more of a trade.

977
01:31:25,110 --> 01:31:26,800
Get me out of here.

978
01:31:29,110 --> 01:31:30,990
No!

979
01:31:31,060 --> 01:31:32,920
There, there, Caroline.

980
01:31:45,560 --> 01:31:49,580
We thought it was just a fall, but
now she can't move or even speak.

981
01:31:50,100 --> 01:31:51,410
Like a stroke or something.

982
01:31:51,480 --> 01:31:52,560
Cary?

983
01:31:53,680 --> 01:31:55,000
Dearie me.

984
01:31:58,610 --> 01:31:59,890
You called me.

985
01:31:59,990 --> 01:32:01,400
I called you?

986
01:32:04,280 --> 01:32:06,420
For help. Don't you remember?

987
01:32:07,320 --> 01:32:10,290
Cary's not herself right now.
I'm Luke Marshall.

988
01:32:10,900 --> 01:32:14,070
- Devereauxs' lawyer.
- Hi. Jill Dupay, her roommate.

989
01:32:14,420 --> 01:32:16,560
Jill, yes, I did call you.

990
01:32:17,170 --> 01:32:19,350
Fiddlesticks.
I don't know what possessed me.

991
01:32:20,700 --> 01:32:22,600
It's all right. I'm here.

992
01:32:24,220 --> 01:32:26,100
They need real care now.

993
01:32:26,780 --> 01:32:28,410
They can't stay here.

994
01:32:28,470 --> 01:32:30,200
This is all my fault.

995
01:32:30,270 --> 01:32:31,960
No, Cary. No, it's not.

996
01:32:32,800 --> 01:32:34,010
It's not.

997
01:32:44,060 --> 01:32:47,450
Someone should ride
to the hospital with them. Maybe...

998
01:32:48,160 --> 01:32:51,670
Jill, would you mind? And we'll meet you.

999
01:32:53,500 --> 01:32:55,230
Of course. Whatever you need.

1000
01:33:02,430 --> 01:33:05,910
She meant so much to them, her being here.

1001
01:33:07,170 --> 01:33:09,080
I know it wasn't for long, but...

1002
01:33:10,630 --> 01:33:12,220
they really loved her.

1003
01:33:13,320 --> 01:33:14,520
Why do you say that?

1004
01:33:19,840 --> 01:33:21,540
It's in their wills.

1005
01:33:22,250 --> 01:33:24,130
They left her the house.

